Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 4/3/00

We learned from SeaChanges that they are going to use a repeated
advertisement as the network feed in the NAB show.  However, the
dpi code died right at the wrap around point.  We figured out that
this is due to a bug in the clean cut module.  Wayne has already
fixed the problem.

Although our code will not die immediately at the wrap around point,
the short dead time at wrap around will introduce DTS jump, which the
statmux is not designed to handle as normal operation.  It will handle
it as an error case, but may have long term effect that we have not fully
tested.  As a result, our box may not be able to run reliably for a long
time.  I have asked Sangeeta to look into this problem, but this fix will
take quite some time.

SeaChange also reported that our output stream gives an unstable picture
on their decoder box.  We believe that this is due to the PCR jitter
problem that we have already been aware of.  Jin Churn later found the
bug which causes the problem.  The problem has now been fixed.

In our testing I saw several cases of bad pointer problem when rate
conversion is turned on.  I rewrote the interface part of rate
conversion module.  The problem is fixed now.

I have added some code to automatically detect stack overflow problems.
With this I found that some tasks have this problem.  I have resize
the stacks for those tasks, and also re-prioritize the tasks.  The
reliability of the code is improved. 

On March 28, we released the latest version of our codes to SeaChange
for their NAB demos.


